    <sampling_method>Non-Probability Sample</sampling_method>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Age &gt; 18 - &lt; 60 years

          -  Patients underwent elective spine surgery

          -  ASA classification 1-3

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients who have the concomitant condition

          -  Cancer

          -  History of heart disease including, heart failure, coronary artery disease,
             hypertension treated with more than one medicament.

          -  Serum creatinine &gt; 1.5 mg/dL

          -  Stroke, neurologic and mental deficits, epilepsy

          -  General or local infection (site of surgery),

          -  Coagulation disorders.

          -  Intraoperative massive bleeding

          -  Infection of the spine

          -  Rheumatoid arthritis

          -  Patients who had either of the following drug (aspirin, methotrexate, cyclosporine,
             qualaquin)
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
